{"lemma":"صَدْعِ","slug":"صَدْعِ","root":"ص.د.ع","root_slug":"ص-د-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-د-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَدْع","root":"صدع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n23956","n23957","n23958"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to crack","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have a headache"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crack"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fault, fissure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَدَعَ (ṣadaʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23956","headword_ar":"صَدْعٌ","root":"SdE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally an inf. n.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cleft, split, slit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, O, K, TA,) [generally] in a hard thing, (Lth, O, K, TA,) such as a glass vessel, and a wall, and the like of these: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuduwEN","text_ar":"صُدُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hassán says, satirizing El-Hárith Ibn-'Owf El-Murree,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA^amaAnapu Almur~iY~i Hayovu laqiytahu\n                      \n                     \n                        mivolu Alz~ujaAjapi SadoEuhaA lamo yujobari"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the fidelity of the Murree, where"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wherever"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou meetest him, is like the glass vessel, of which the crack is not repaired"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, separated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing, (O, K, TA,) of sheep or goats, and the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1664},{"kind":"text","text":"like: (TA:) an inf. n. used as a subst. [properly thus termed]: (O, K, TA:) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqN","text_ar":"خَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoluwqN","text_ar":"مَخْلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c. (O, TA.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plants of the earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) because they cleave it: (TA:) [i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plants from over which the earth cleaves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@lA^aroDi *aAti A@lS~adoEi","text_ar":"وَا@لاَرْضِ ذَاتِ ا@لصَّدْعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur lxxxvi. 12: (Bd:) or this phrase means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the earth which is cloven"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the plants (Th, Bd, TA) and by the springs. (Bd.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilobN","text_ar":"اـِلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu Ealayohimo","text_ar":"النَّاسُ عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadoEN waAHid","text_ar":"صَدْعٌ وَاحِد"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilobN waAHidN","text_ar":"اـِلْبٌ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alobN","text_ar":"اَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidN","text_ar":"وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people are one company combined in hostility against them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEolN wAHd","text_ar":"وَعْلٌ واحد"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DilaEN wAHd","text_ar":"ضِلَعٌ واحد"},{"kind":"text","text":": so says AZ. (TA.)       -A3-  And A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of flesh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaEN","text_ar":"صَدَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) sometimes: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of middling stature, light of flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the mountain-goat thus termed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaEN","text_ar":"صَدَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Lth","S","O","K","TA","Bd","Th","Ks"]},{"entry_id":"n23957","headword_ar":"صِدْعٌ","root":"SdE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing that is cloven, or split, or slit, in halves. (K, * TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SidoEapN","text_ar":"صِدْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaEa Al$~aYo'a SidoEayoni","text_ar":"صَدَعَ الشَّىْءَ صِدْعَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"split,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slit, the thing in halves."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company of men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, O, K.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman who makes a division in the state of a people and does not repair it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn- 'Abbád, O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n23958","headword_ar":"صَدَعٌ","root":"SdE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadoEN","text_ar":"صَدْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the former only, (S,) applied to a mountain-goat, and a gazelle, and an ass, [app. a wild ass,] (S, K,) and a camel, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of a middling size, neither great nor small, but between the two:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"youthful and strong:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyEN","text_ar":"صَدِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or [in the CK “ and ”] the former word signifies a thing of any sort"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between two things; between tall and short,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"youthful and advanced in age,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat and lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great and small."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  For the former word as applied to a man: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadoEN","text_ar":"صَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Also, thus applied"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Penetrating, sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effective, in his affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  [It is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaEN","text_ar":"صَدَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaA^","text_ar":"صَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rust"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of iron. (K.) [But this seems to be a mistake, which has arisen from what here follows.] It is said that [a certain person called] El-Uskuff [which generally means “ the bishop ”], being asked by 'Omar respecting the Khaleefehs, designated [him who was afterwards] the fourth of them ['Alee] as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaEN mino HadiydK","text_ar":"صَدَعٌ مِنْ حَدِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning [lit.] thereby"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mountain-goat of iron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"using it as a hyperbolical appellation to denote his might and courage and endurance and hardness: or the phrase, as some relate it, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaA^N HadydN","text_ar":"صَدَاٌ حَديدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which may be rendered, “ light or active in body ” (a meaning assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaA^N","text_ar":"صَدَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaEN","text_ar":"صَدَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter of which is said to be in this sense the original), and “ sharp ”]; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaA^u HadiydK","text_ar":"صَدَاُ حَدِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. “ rust of iron, ” app. alluding to his frequent and long-continued wearing of mail and bearing of weapons]; which last is thought by As to be most probably correct. (O, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}